    }
  ],
  "remarks": "Aleksandr Livshits is Deputy of the State Council of the Republic of Tatarstan as well as a member of the Presidium of the State Council of the Republic of Tatarstan; the General Director of the Federal State Enterprise Kazan State-Owned Gunpowder Plant (FKP KGKPZ), which produces a variety of pyroxylin powders and charges for almost all types of weapons. FKP KGKPZ manufactures 5,45 -14,5  mm caliber cartridges for rifles (Kalashnikov assault rifles), grenade launcher charges, propellant charges for naval cannons (AK-100, AK-130 and AK-726) and land artillery of 76 mm to 152 mm caliber (mortars 2S9 and 2S12, howitzers D-20, D-30, ML-20, 2S1, 2S3 and 2S19). The plant produces 115 mm, 122 mm and, most importantly, 125 mm caliber tank ammunition, which is used in the T-64, T-72, T-80 and T-90 tanks of the Russian Armed Forces. FKP KGKPZ supplies ammunition to the Russian Armed Forces and their weapon systems used in the war in Ukraine.",
  "birth_info": [
